### -------------------------
### GRANOLA LOCAL API TESTS
### -------------------------

# Instructions:
# 1. Use an extension like "REST Client" in VS Code to run these requests.
# 2. Run the Auth tests first to get a JWT token.
# 3. Paste the JWT token into the @token variable below.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = RUN USER LOGIN AND GET AND PASTE TOKEN HERE FROM RESPONSE

### -------------------------
### AUTHENTICATION API
### -------------------------

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### 2. Login
### -> Copy the token from the response and paste it into @token above!
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword"
}


### -------------------------
### HEALTH & UTILS
### -------------------------

### Health Check (Public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### CORS Preflight (Checks if CORS is working)
OPTIONS {{baseUrl}}/api/notes
Origin: http://localhost:5173
Access-Control-Request-Method: GET


### -------------------------
### NOTES (CRUD API)
### NOTE: All these require the Bearer @token set above
### -------------------------

### 1. Get All Notes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Create a Note 
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/notes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My New Meeting Note",
  "content": "This is successfully writing to the Postgres database for this authenticated user!"
}

### 4. Create a Note (Invalid - Wrong Data Type)
### Title has a built-in default, so omitting it is valid. 
### To trigger a Zod error, we must send the WRONG data type.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/notes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": 123,
  "content": "A number cannot be a title!"
}

### 5. Update a Note (Partial Update / PATCH)
### -> REPLACE :noteId with a real note ID from the Get All Notes response
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/:note-id
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Title via PATCH!",
  "content": "Old content was replaced."
}

### 6. Delete a Note
### -> REPLACE :noteId with a real note ID from the Get All Notes response
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/:noteId
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
